<section>
    <h2>Project Details</h2>
    <div class="project-details">
        <p>This project is a full-featured e-commerce web application for beauty products. Users can browse products, add them to the cart, and simulate checkout. The admin panel allows product management and order tracking.</p>
        <p>The main goals of this project are to demonstrate:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Full-stack development using Java, JSP, and MySQL</li>
            <li>Responsive web design for desktop and mobile</li>
            <li>Database integration with JPA</li>
            <li>Clean and maintainable code structure</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
</section>

<section>
    <h2>Tech Stack</h2>
    <div class="tech-stack">
        <span class="tech-tag">Java</span>
        <span class="tech-tag">JSP</span>
        <span class="tech-tag">MySQL</span>
        <span class="tech-tag">GlassFish</span>
        <span class="tech-tag">JPA</span>
        <span class="tech-tag">HTML/CSS/JS</span>
    </div>
</section>

<section>
    <h2>How to Run Locally</h2>
    <p>Clone the repository, open in NetBeans, build with Ant, and deploy on GlassFish:</p>
    <pre>
git clone https://github.com/Wanqi0225/BeautyProductsEcommerce.git
Open build.xml in NetBeans
Clean & Build
Deploy to GlassFish
    </pre>
</section>

